{
  "stem": "26142.6",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He will wait until it gets darker in the evening hours, 7, 8 o'clock, you know, summertime.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he let-- let us stay there, and he-- and he left.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Of course, we were kind of leery.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We didn't know if-- if he is going to keep his-- his promise but we had no choice.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We had no other choice but to wait.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we stayed there and by 7 o'clock or so he did come.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He did come.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We gave him the agreed price, the blanket and-- and a pair of underpants.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And he put-- he put Moshe, my sister-in-law, and the two children on the wagon and we walked alongside.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he brought us to a place called [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Istichka. ?] At the outskirt of the place there was a Jewish widow that lived there and evidently he knew her and that was the closest for him and he dumped us off over there.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "That widow lived with a daughter and son-in-law in that house.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they were very gracious.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They took us in.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They had a room and they took us into their-- to their house.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And we found out that in this place, [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Istichka. ?] There is-- there is Hungarian troops come and go there and they stay some of them there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "That for Hungarian money, the soldiers, you can buy from them, they would sell cigarettes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They would sell conserves that they would have.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And cigarettes, that was the currency doing the wartime.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "For some reason, for cigarettes you could buy anything.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So anyway, we stayed in this place in [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Istichka ?] somewhere-- Somewhere between 10 and 12 days.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- the two women-- the two women were, they had to go out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The son-in-law, his name must have been Leif or Levi.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
